Large-scale millers are not receiving maize from farmers because of the drought.Yesterday, Cereal Millers&rsquo; Association chairman Nick Hutchinson said, &ldquo;We are unable to get maize. The government started taking stock of maize in the country on Friday last week,&rdquo;he said.He said no cases of hoarding have been reported.Last week, Agriculture CS Willy Bett warned people against hoarding maize, adding that they will face unspecified consequences.&ldquo;We are giving them a week to release the maize, &rdquo; he told the Star on the phone. Bett said an assessment will be done to determine whether the country needs to import maize.